---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PillarCard from '../components/PillarCard.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<BaseLayout title="Age of Abundance" description="In the age of AI, far more is possible. Practical projects for a world where everyone has the basics — and government tells the truth.">
  <section class="container hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">A project about the world we could choose</p>
    <h1>The Age of Abundance</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      In the age of AI, far more is possible than ever before. We could build a world where
      everyone has the basics — a secure home, enough food, real access to education and health
      care — and where government is honest about what it stands for.
    </p>
    <p class="lede" style="font-size:1.05rem;">
      This site holds two practical projects working toward that. One is about how we
      <strong>govern</strong>. The other is about how we <strong>house</strong> each other.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="pillars">
      <PillarCard
        href={`${base}/open-government`}
        eyebrow="Project 1 · How we govern"
        title="Open Government"
        body="Publicly state the world you want and the priorities you hold — then let anyone check whether the laws you support actually match. A simple antidote to spin, and a foundation for a truth era."
        cta="Read the idea →"
      />
      <PillarCard
        href={`${base}/affordable-housing`}
        eyebrow="Project 2 · How we house"
        title="Affordable Housing Company"
        body="A group pools cash to buy a rental home outright — no debt — through a shared company and unit trust. It opens property to ordinary people and takes a home out of the speculative market."
        cta="See the model →"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="callout">
      <span class="callout-title">A core belief running through both</span>
      <p>
        Government's first duty is to the people who would otherwise miss out — not to give a leg-up
        to those already winning. A society is failing when it does the latter. Both projects here are
        attempts to take real action toward the former.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p style="color:var(--text-soft); font-size:0.95rem;">
      Age of Abundance is an evolving personal project by Kris. These pages explain each idea simply,
      then drill all the way down into how it could actually be done. You're welcome to take any of it
      and make it your own.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
